Data Scientist		Conversant Inc.		Chicago, IL		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Data Scientist <br /><br /> Chicago, IL, United States <br /><br /> Full-time <br /><br /> Your role <br /><br /> Conversant’s business is based on analysis of anonymized data at internet scale, and is used in evaluating more than 1 trillion advertising opportunities per month – in real-time. As a Data Scientist in our R&amp;D organization, you will be responsible for analyzing our proprietary data and collaborating with research teams to solve real-world problems and extend Conversant’s personalization platform. This includes researching and developing models, algorithms, and applications; analyzing raw source data and derived data; presenting findings; and building tools to provide instrumentation and real-time analysis statistics for new and existing products. You will work within our highly collaborative R&amp;D team. Your solutions will directly and rapidly impact our business! <br /><br /> Your responsibilities <br /><br /> · Develop a deep understanding of Conversant’s personalization platform and proprietary datasets <br /><br /> · Research and develop metrics and KPIs that measure the impact of new technologies <br /><br /> · Research and develop automated data analyses for monitoring continuous business processes <br /><br /> · Research and develop techniques to identify bots and other suspicious behavior using data science, predictive modeling, and/or machine learning <br /><br /> · Learn to use tools such as Scala and Apache Spark for high-level distributed parallel programming <br /><br /> · Participate fully in our collaborative approach to R&amp;D and applications <br /><br /> Ideal candidates will have the following qualifications <br /><br /> · Masters or Ph.D. in an analytical discipline such as applied mathematics, statistics, computer science, machine learning, engineering, sciences <br /><br /> · Fluency in programming <br /><br /> · Experience in database languages such as SQL <br /><br /> · R&amp;D experience or coursework in data science, data mining, or data analysis <br /><br /> · R&amp;D experience or coursework in applied mathematics, statistics, predictive modeling, machine learning, or artificial intelligence <br /><br /> · Experience in a technical work environment is preferred <br /><br /> · Experience with big data a plus <br /><br /> · Experience in parallelized algorithms or distributed computing is a plus <br /><br /> · Experience or coursework in experimental design a plus <br /><br /> · Strong verbal and written communication skills <br /><br /> · Desire to work in a dynamic, fast paced environment with multiple simultaneous projects <br /><br /><strong>Qualifications</strong><br /><br /><strong>Conditions of Employment</strong> <br />All job offers are contingent upon successful completion of certain background checks which unless prohibited by applicable law may include criminal history checks, employment verification, education verification, drug screens, credit checks, DMV checks (for driving positions only) and fingerprinting.<br /><br /><strong>About Conversant</strong> <br />Conversant, Inc. is the leader in personalized digital marketing. Conversant helps the world's biggest companies grow by creating personalized experiences that deliver higher returns for brands and greater satisfaction for people. We offer a fully integrated personalization platform, personalized media programs and the world's largest affiliate marketing network - all fueled by a deep understanding of what motivates people to engage, connect and buy. For more information, please visit http://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=http://www.conversantmedia.com&amp;esheet=50979797&amp;newsitemid=20141107006050&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=www.conversantmedia.com&amp;index=1&amp;md5=ceffa9dd43ffb213f30808148e513ad7 .<br /><br /><strong>Great People, Deserve Great Benefits</strong> <br />We know that we have some of the